PREFACE=20


On April 1, 1924,1 entered upon my prison term in the fortress=20
of Landsberg am Lech, as sentenced by the People=E2=80=99s Court in=20
Munich on that day.=20

Thus, after years of uninterrupted work, an opportunity was=20
for the first time offered me to embark upon a task which many=20
had demanded and which I myself felt to be worth while for the=20
movement. I decided to set forth, in two volumes, the aims of=20
our movement, and also to draw a picture of its development.=20
From this it will be possible to learn more than from any purely=20
doctrinaire treatise.=20

At the same time I have had occasion to give an account of my=20
own development, in so far as this is necessary for the under=C2=AC=20
standing of the first as well as the second volume, and in so far=20
as it may serve to destroy the foul legends about my person dished=20
up in the Jewish press.=20

I do not address this work to strangers, but to those adherents=20
of the movement who belong to it with their hearts, and whose=20
intelligence is eager for a more penetrating enlightenment. I=20
know that men are won over less by the written than by the=20
spoken word, that every great movement on this earth owes its=20
growth to great orators and not to great writers.=20

Nevertheless, for a doctrine to be disseminated uniformly and=20
coherently, its basic elements must be set down for all time. To=20
this end I wish to contribute these two volumes as foundation=20
stones in our common edifice.=20

